    <main>
      <section class="bg-[#FAFAFA] pb-[80px] pt-[calc(var(--header-height,72px)+80px)] lg:pt-[222px] lg:pb-[150px] lg:px-[256px]">
        <div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-[40px] font-['Shippori_Mincho'] px-[16px] lg:px-0 lg:gap-[80px]">
          <h1 class="text-center text-[32px] leading-[48px] tracking-[3.6px] text-[#436C5E] font-medium lg:w-[480px] lg:text-[36px] lg:leading-[54px]">
            Accommodation Agreement
          </h1>
          <div class="text-left text-[14px] leading-[22.75px] tracking-[2.1px] text-[#483F38] whitespace-pre-line lg:text-left lg:w-full lg:text-[16px] lg:leading-[32px] lg:tracking-[1.6px]">aoshima tei SUZU
            Accommodation Agreement (for website / full version)

            These Accommodation Terms (the "Terms") set forth the conditions for lodging services provided by aoshima tei SUZU (the "Property").
            By making a reservation or using the Property, the guest agrees to all provisions of these Terms.

            Article 1 (Scope)
            These Terms apply to all lodging contracts and related use between the Property and guests.
            Matters not stipulated herein shall be governed by the Ryokan Business Act, related laws, the MLIT Model Accommodation Terms (latest revision), and established customs.

            Article 2 (Formation of the Lodging Contract)
            The lodging contract is concluded when the Property accepts the reservation.
            Any changes to stay date, number of guests, or usage details must be reported in advance and approved by the Property.

            Article 3 (Check-in / Check-out)
            Check-in and check-out times are as determined by the Property.
            Unauthorized overstay may result in additional charges or treatment as illegal stay.

            Article 4 (Number of Guests and Use Restrictions)
            Only the number of guests declared at booking is permitted; exceeding capacity is not allowed for any reason.
            Adding guests without notice, inviting third parties, or allowing visitors to stay overnight or for extended periods is prohibited.
            Use for parties, banquets, or events is prohibited.
            In case of violation, the Property may terminate the contract without notice and require immediate departure; no refunds will be provided.

            Article 5 (Nighttime Use and Noise)
            As the Property is located in a residential area, please keep quiet after 9:00 PM and early morning.
            Loud conversations, music playback, or outdoor gatherings that disturb neighbors are prohibited.
            If complaints are received, the Property may terminate the contract without warning.

            Article 6 (Consideration for Neighbors)
            Guests must respect the living environment of local residents and refrain from any nuisance.
            The Property may issue corrective instructions or terminate the contract in response to complaints or reports.

            Article 7 (Valuables and Lost Items)
            Guests are responsible for managing their valuables.
            Lost items will be stored for up to 7 days and then disposed of or handed to the police.

            Article 8 (Handling of Trash)
            Please follow the designated sorting method and disposal location.
            Disposal of large amounts of trash, bulky items, or trash brought from outside the Property is prohibited.

            Article 9 (Facilities and Amenities)
            Furniture, equipment, and amenities are carefully selected, and may include rare or non-replaceable items.
            Guests must use all items with due care.
            In case of damage, staining, or loss, actual costs including repair, replacement, or import fees will be charged.
            If monetary compensation is insufficient, resolution will be discussed at the Property's discretion.

            Article 10 (Cleaning and Restoration)
            If excessive soiling, odor, vomit, or oil stains are found beyond normal cleaning, special cleaning fees will be charged.
            If restoration is difficult, damages including repair and business loss may be claimed.

            Article 11 (Natural Environment)
            As the Property is in a natural environment, refunds or compensation will not be provided for insects, animals, weather, or natural sounds.

            Article 12 (Disasters and Outages)
            No refunds or compensation will be provided for disruptions caused by typhoons, earthquakes, power outages, water outages, or communication failures.

            Article 13 (Parking)
            The Property bears no responsibility for accidents, theft, or damage within the parking area.

            Article 14 (Exclusion of Anti-Social Forces)
            Use by organized crime groups or other anti-social forces is strictly prohibited; the contract will be terminated immediately if identified.

            Article 15 (Compliance and Liability)
            If a guest violates laws or these Terms and causes damage to the Property or third parties, the guest bears full responsibility.

            Article 16 (Cancellation Policy)
            The following cancellation fees will be charged.
            No-show / No-arrival: 100% of the accommodation fee
            Same-day cancellation: 100%
            Up to 3 days prior: 80%
            Up to 15 days prior: 50%
            Up to 30 days prior: 30%

            Article 17 (Governing Law and Jurisdiction)
            These Terms are governed by the laws of Japan, and disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the court with jurisdiction over the Property's location.
